security-r8-audio-11: don't open a graphical console window in
`crosvm device gpu`.

Port of talex5/crosvm@993b8e756 ("Don't open a graphical console
window") to the vhost-user-gpu backend path. Upstream's patch
landed against the in-tree GPU device at
src/crosvm/sys/linux/gpu.rs (used by `crosvm run`); the equivalent
code in devices/src/virtio/vhost_user_backend/gpu/sys/linux.rs is
what `crosvm device gpu` exercises.

Symptom: a transparent, chromeless window titled "crosvm" with no
WM_CLASS appears on the host compositor every time a graphics-enabled
VM starts. KDE Plasma renders it without decoration (crosvm never
requests xdg-decoration SSD) and labels it with the default "W"
placeholder icon. The window stays visible for the lifetime of the
VM. The DisplayParameters.hidden field that microvm.nix passes is
silently ignored on Linux/Wayland.

The upstream author who designed the original cross-domain forwarding
model hit the same artifact and dropped the Wayland + X DisplayBackends
entirely, leaving Stub as the only backend. The scanout protocol still
works against Stub (it discards SetScanout silently); the guest's
virtio_gpu driver gets RESP_OK and proceeds. Cross-domain Wayland
forwarding is independent of the scanout backend and unaffected.

